===Etymology 1===
; “a kind of big bean”
: Cognate with {{cog|my|ညံ||the legume {{taxlink|Sesbania cannabina|species}}}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). Sagart alternatively links this to {{m+|tbq-pro|*s-n(u/a)m|t=fat, oil}}, presuming that {{w|perilla oil}} was known to early Sinitic peoples ([https://stan.hypotheses.org/1417 Sagart, 2021]).

; “soft; weak”
: From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*njam||soft}}. Cognate with {{cog|my|ညံ့||soft}}, {{cog|lus|nêm||soft}}. Outside Sino-Tibetan, compare {{cog|th|นุ่ม||soft}}.
: Possibly related to {{och-l|飪|cooked}}, {{och-l|腍|cooked; delicious}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).
: Older theories compare the word with {{och-l|柔|soft}} (STEDT).

